#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.108"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.108:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.108:0.2"
msgid "11. Yogakkhemivagga "
msgstr "11. Sanctuary "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 108. Seyyohamasmisutta → seyyasuttaṃ (bj) | seyyo (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.108:0.3"
msgid "108. Seyyohamasmisutta "
msgstr "108. I’m Better "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.88, sc1
msgctxt "sn35.108:1.1"
msgid "“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati kiṃ upādāya kiṃ abhinivissa seyyohamasmīti vā hoti, sadisohamasmīti vā hoti, hīnohamasmīti vā hotī”ti? "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, do people think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.108:2.1"
msgid "“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …. "
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.108:3.1"
msgid "“Cakkhusmiṃ kho, bhikkhave, sati cakkhuṃ upādāya cakkhuṃ abhinivissa seyyohamasmīti vā hoti, sadisohamasmīti vā hoti, hīnohamasmīti vā hoti … pe … "
msgstr "“When there’s an eye, because of grasping the eye and insisting on the eye, people think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’. … "

msgctxt "sn35.108:3.2"
msgid "jivhāya sati … pe … "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.108:3.3"
msgid "manasmiṃ sati manaṃ upādāya manaṃ abhinivissa seyyohamasmīti vā hoti, sadisohamasmīti vā hoti, hīnohamasmīti vā hoti. "
msgstr "When there’s a mind, because of grasping the mind and insisting on the mind, people think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.108:3.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn35.108:3.5"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.108:4.1"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn35.108:5.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.108:6.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn35.108:7.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya seyyohamasmīti vā assa, sadisohamasmīti vā assa, hīnohamasmīti vā assā”ti? "
msgstr "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would people think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn35.108:8.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante” … pe … "
msgstr "“No, sir.” … "

msgctxt "sn35.108:8.2"
msgid "jivhā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn35.108:8.3"
msgid "niccā vā aniccā vā”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn35.108:9.1"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante” … pe …. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn35.108:10.1"
msgid "“Mano nicco vā anicco vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Is the mind permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn35.108:11.1"
msgid "“Anicco, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn35.108:12.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn35.108:13.1"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "sn35.108:14.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya seyyohamasmīti vā assa, sadisohamasmīti vā assa, hīnohamasmīti vā assā”ti? "
msgstr "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would people think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "sn35.108:15.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "sn35.108:16.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati … pe … manasmimpi nibbindati. "
msgstr "“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind. "

msgctxt "sn35.108:16.2"
msgid "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.108:16.3"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.108:16.4"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

